I think its just honda stock things
What happens if u do both
Springs go over your stock damper
Coil is a full set by itself
Ahh so that means it will not have any issue within themselves?
Coilovers are already a full assembly that is adjustable
Lowering springs replace your stock springs but u keep your damper
It depends on what u want ultimately
Lowering springs are cost effective aesthetic change but directly translates to a harsher ride
Because u just effectively used back a stock damper and now your travel is shorter
The damper is not optimized for that set up
Hence it will damage ur damper
Coils are the so called ‚Äúproper‚Äù way to do it
Since it comes with mounts and dampers that were meant for it
Or u can do the opposite of what ppl do
And change the damper and roll like a conti
